<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 07 at 7:43PM EST  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...Patchy Black Ice Expected Tuesday Morning...
Rain and drizzle will end across the area late this evening.
However, temperatures will fall into the upper 20s to lower 30s
overnight and areas of black ice will be possible around daybreak
mainly west of Interstate 95. Conditions should improve by mid
morning once temperatures rise above freezing.
Black ice is difficult to see. Use caution while walking and
traveling.</description>
